@startuml PageLocs_Hardened_Lifecycle_States
  title PageLocs Hardened Lifecycle State Machine

  state Idle
  state Starting
  state Running
  state Draining
  state Stopped
  state Failed

  [*] --> Idle
  Idle --> Starting : openBook()
  Starting --> Running : setup succeeded
  Starting --> Failed : setup failed
  Running --> Draining : stopControlTask()
  Running --> Failed : fatal error (queue, thread, map)
  Draining --> Stopped : STOPPED received
  Draining --> Failed : timeout or unrecoverable error
  Stopped --> Idle : openBook() (new doc)
  Failed --> Idle : recover/reset

  Running --> Running : navigation, ASAP, percent queries
  Running --> Running : background computation
  Running --> Failed : queue full, send/recv error, map corruption

  note right of Starting
    - Allocates queues, threads, map
    - Handles setup errors
  end note
  note right of Running
    - Accepts navigation, ASAP, percent
    - Handles background computation
    - All map access under strict mutex
    - All requests have correlation IDs
  end note
  note right of Draining
    - Sends STOP, waits for STOPPED
    - Bounded wait, diagnostics on timeout
  end note
  note right of Failed
    - All API calls return error
    - Only recover/reset allowed
  end note
@enduml
